CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 17, 1951, pg. 3, reads: "Good Hunting - L. P. Newson, C. C. Poinsette and Thomas Clemens recently returned from a one week hunting excursion in the woods around Patten, Me.  With them they brought two bears shown draped on the fenders of the automobile. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Thomas Clemens, C. C. Poinsette, and Len P. Newson, posed around Buick car with two dead bears and guns, on street
